OL,4,C'The Taliban killed my brother for
OL,5,Cprotecting my family'
OL,6, While watching the country he grew up
OL,7, in descend into chaos, Saba got the
OL,8, call he had been dreading. His family
OL,9, told him "the Taliban are trying to
OL,10, burn down my house and asking for my
OL,11, brother", he said. Nothing he had seen
OL,12, before could have prepared him for what
OL,13, happened next.
OL,15,FSaba, who lives in London, left
OL,16,FAfghanistan two decades ago to escape
OL,17,Fthe previous Taliban regime.
OL,19,FHis family stayed and made a new life
OL,20,Fafter the Taliban were deposed in the
OL,21,FAfghanistan War.
